      "review_highlights": [
        {
          "comment": "Overall, he's a bore with weekly PAPERS and an even more complex and pointless final project! Repeatedly submitting something is simply pointless, he is very untimely in giving out grades and only follows the grading rubric form without any useful comments, take his class ready for inexplicable colloquialisms and a lot of pointless work, run!!!!!!",
          "class_name": "UGPH-50",
          "grade": "Not sure yet",
          "date": "2025-05-04",
          "clarity": 2,
          "helpful": 2,
          "difficulty": 5,
          "score": 3.8491095890410962
        },
        {
          "comment": "Professor Amegbor was understanding and informative. He does read from slides which can be monotonous. But he does try to make it engaging and funny at some moments. The course assignments and grading policy are clear. There are 2 reflection papers due every week on various environmental health topics, like built environment and noise pollution.",
          "class_name": "UGPH-50",
          "grade": "A-",
          "date": "2024-08-08",
          "clarity": 4,
