      "review_highlights": [
        {
          "comment": "Fall 2015 was Andys first semester at NYU, he is very young and comes across as super excited and wanting to share absolutely everything he knows. This desire to share leads to many tangents and for the student, much confusion. Also, has a bad habit of using American football to illustrate examples.",
          "class_name": "STATS101",
          "grade": "",
          "date": "2015-03-24",
          "clarity": 1,
          "helpful": 2,
          "difficulty": 5,
          "score": 6.5
        },
        {
          "comment": "I would not take this professor ever again. For example, there were questions on the exam from optional readings; optional readings! Oh, and there were 2 midterms. Takes himself way too seriously and grades like you're his own kid. This is a graduate course, where assignments aren't supposed to be graded as harshly.",
          "class_name": "101",
          "grade": "B",
          "date": "2015-05-29",
          "clarity": 1,
          "helpful": 3,
          "difficulty": 5,
          "score": 5.585
        },
        {
          "comment": "Andy's class is tough in some ways: the midterm is long, the homework is nearly incomprehensible if you skip lab, and the final project is pretty serious for an undergraduate course. However, he's a super fair grader and extraordinarily kind, patient person who does his best to make stats accessible and interesting. One of the best at NYU!",
          "class_name": "UPADMGP111",
          "grade": "A",
          "date": "2018-02-11",
          "clarity": 5,
          "helpful": 5,
          "difficulty": 3,
          "score": 1.705
        },
        {
          "comment": "Took him for Politics of PP. Super nice and knowledgeable guy but class can drag on sometimes since it's almost 3 hours long. I didn't really read toward the end of the semester and still did well on the exam/assignments. My recommendation is go over the slides and pay attention to the real-world examples he gives for the material.",
          "class_name": "UPADMGP101",
          "grade": "A",
          "date": "2017-04-12",
          "clarity": 4,
          "helpful": 4,
          "difficulty": 3,
          "score": 1.665
        },
        {
          "comment": "His class was pretty tough considering that it's stat 1&2 material in one semester but prof Sinclair really does want you to do well in class and is very accessible and fair. Once you dig through all the information he gives you (which is a LOT, relevant or not) the class is really interesting. Plus his TA Brett is really helpful.",
          "class_name": "UPADMGP111",
          "grade": "",
